articles.title: Insurer agrees to $800M settlement in Boy Scouts bankruptcy - Associated Press
articles.description: DOVER, Del. (AP) — Attorneys in the Boy Scouts of America bankruptcy case have reached a tentative settlement under which one of the organization’s largest insurers would contribute $800 million into a fund for victims of child sexual abuse.
